<HEADLINE>
<P>
TONY SERRA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I am enraged at Tony Serra's statement that people killed by drug overdoses and 
infants born addicted to drugs are expendable. 
</P>
<P>
Has this man no concern for human life? 
</P>
<P>
I am also appalled that such a self-righteous crusader for justice flouts the 
laws against drugs, deliberately does not pay parking tickets and for many 
years did not file a tax return. 
</P>
<P>
There are two words for people like Serra, and those words are criminal and 
hypocrite. Serra is just as bad as the people he rails against who hunted down 
and killed Indians like coyotes. 
</P>
<P>
ROBERT E. PARK 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
