<HEADLINE>
<P>
TONY SERRA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I spent 15 years in the world of drugs, six of those years with drug smugglers 
and dealers. 
</P>
<P>
I watched my friends go from vital, creative human beings to zombies. I watched 
them get murdered, overdose, go to jail and destroy their families. 
</P>
<P>
Every time Tony Serra gets his drug clients off, he might as well hand them a 
shovel to dig their graves and the graves of the people they sell to. 
</P>
<P>
Last week another person I cared about died -- another person with a name, a 
face and loved ones. Maybe that's "small" to Tony Serra because it isn't 
happening to his family. 
</P>
<P>
PAMELA BARRETT 
</P>
<P>
San Diego 
</P>
</TEXT>
