<HEADLINE>
<P>
TIMES TELEVISION GUIDE EXPANDS CABLE COVERAGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Los Angeles Times Valley Edition and West Valley Cablevision have entered 
into an agreement for The Times to produce a newly expanded, weekly television 
guide with broadcast and cable television listings and features. 
</P>
<P>
The new book, a redesigned version of TV Times, will be available in all copies 
of The Times delivered or sold in the area served by West Valley Cablevision. 
</P>
<P>
That area includes communities north of Ventura Boulevard, west of the San 
Diego Freeway to the county line and north to Granada Hills. Jeff Hall, 
president of The Times Valley and Ventura County editions, said the redesigned 
TV Times guide will be "colorful, easy to use and more comprehensive than any 
other guide available." 
</P>
<P>
Tom Belcher, executive vice president and general manager of West Valley 
Cablevision, said, "I look forward to working with The Times in providing this 
guide, which will give our customers many benefits and advantages previous 
books were not able to offer." 
</P>
<P>
Hall added that he expected to be able to make similar announcements regarding 
new system-specific program guides for other area cable companies within a few 
weeks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
