<HEADLINE>
<P>
VAN NUYS MAN KILLED IN BRAWL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Van Nuys man died Saturday morning from injuries he received in a barroom 
brawl in North Hollywood, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Leo Firpo, 25, was punched and kicked by two assailants and at 1:35 a.m. was 
left lying unconscious in the parking lot of FM Station, a nightclub at 11700 
Victory Blvd. in North Hollywood, said Los Angeles Police Sgt. Christopher 
Vasquez. 
</P>
<P>
Firpo was driven by a friend to the Medical Center of North Hollywood, where he 
died at 2:22 a.m., Vasquez said. 
</P>
<P>
Police are searching for two men who beat Firpo, Vasquez said. One is described 
as white, about 5 feet, 8 inches tall and between 25 and 30 years old. Police 
said he was wearing his brown hair in a ponytail and has a large tattoo, 
possibly of a bird, on the left side of his back. The other suspect is 
described as white, between 25 and 27 years old, with brown shoulder-length 
hair. 
</P>
<P>
Witnesses reported that after beating Firpo, the men jumped into the bed of a 
full-size white pickup truck and escaped with a third suspect at the wheel. 
Police have no description of the driver, Vasquez said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<CORRECTION-DATE>
<P>
August 14, 1990, Tuesday, Valley Edition 
</P>
</CORRECTION-DATE>
<CORRECTION>
<P>
FOR THE RECORD 
</P>
<P>
Fatal fight -- An article Sunday incorrectly reported that a Van Nuys man died 
as a result of injuries he received during a fight in FM Station, a nightclub 
in North Hollywood. In fact, the victim, Leo Firpo, was attacked in a parking 
lot outside the bar, police said. 
</P>
</CORRECTION>
