<HEADLINE>
<P>
BARGAIN CORNER: SUNSHINE STATE'S LURES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JACK ADLER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Florida is offering a number of off-season bargains. 
</P>
<P>
Palm Beach has free coupon books through Dec. 20 that are good for discounts, 
two-for-one admissions and complimentary gifts at 95 restaurants, shops, 
sightseeing attractions and sports centers. 
</P>
<P>
For example, you can play a free game of jai alai, pay half-price for 
windsurfing lessons and get sailing discounts on Crown Cruise Line. 
</P>
<P>
If you stay at any of 42 hotels in the Palm Beach area for a week, the seventh 
night is free. 
</P>
<P>
Copies of the "$500 of Palm Beach Free" coupon booklets can be obtained by 
contacting the Palm Beach County Convention and Visitors Bureau at (800) 
242-1774. 
</P>
<P>
If the Key Largo area is your destination, you can obtain a free copy of "Stay 
Down Longer," a coupon booklet offered by the Key Largo Chamber of Commerce. 
The booklet has 67 coupons worth 25% to 50% off at resort hotels, restaurants, 
stores and sightseeing attractions. 
</P>
<P>
Some of the coupons are 2-for-1 deals, while others provide a certain 
percentage off the regular rate. Hotels may offer an extra night free once you 
stay a couple of nights. Coupons are good until the middle of December. 
</P>
<P>
Contact the chamber of commerce at (800) 822-1088. It will mail you a copy of 
the booklet. 
</P>
<P>
Alamo Rent A Car in Florida is offering coupons to renters for a free one-day 
SeaEscape cruise from Ft. Lauderdale/Port Everglades, Miami and St. Petersburg. 
Coupons, good until Dec. 30, are available for as little as one day's car 
rental. Port, service charges and state taxes are extra. 
</P>
<P>
The sailings from Miami or Ft. Lauderdale go to Freeport or Bimini, with a 
port/service/tax charge of $31. The sailing from St. Petersburg is a day-cruise 
for $21. (Regular fares are $89 to Freeport and $79 for the St. Petersburg 
cruise.) Contact Alamo at (800) 327-9633. JACK ADLER 
</P>
</TEXT>
