<P>
GLACIER TRIPS, BOAT RIDES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Laurie Becklund 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Glacier basics: With the exception of the Glacier Bay cruises, you can schedule 
most glacier trips and boat rides while in Alaska. 
</P>
<P>
Unless you want full-scale cruise ship amenities with loungers on deck, look 
for companies offering more maneuverable "yacht-sized" boats. This is one 
situation in which there is no point to looking for off-the-beaten-track 
companies. Most tours end by Sept. 30. 
</P>
<P>
For more information: Brochures are readily available from travel agents and 
Alaska tourism centers: Alaska State Division of Tourism, Box E-101, Juneau, 
Alaska 99811, (907) 465-2010, or the Anchorage Visitor Information Center, 546 
W. Fourth Ave., Anchorage, Alaska 99501, (907) 274-3531. Laurie Becklund 
