<HEADLINE>
<P>
PRESIDENT BUSH SENDS TROOPS TO SAUDI ARABIA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
One idea about the "Butcher of Baghdad" dilemma: Don't kill a lot of civilians, 
etc. Don't even think of committing American ground forces. 
</P>
<P>
Simply station our carriers off Iraq and use missiles alone. What would be the 
target: Very simple -- Saddam Hussein. 
</P>
<P>
We certainly know where his haunts are. We certainly have some kind of 
intelligence inside Iraq. Wherever he goes, wherever he intends to go, blast it 
with a big warhead. I'd be willing to bet he would get real nervous in a short 
time, as Libya's Moammar Kadafi did. Think of the millions of people who would 
have been saved if we could have eliminated Hitler. 
</P>
<P>
Did I hear someone say it's not right to engage in personal assassinations? To 
that I reply that being killed or injured is just as personal to the young men 
now sailing toward harm's way because of this ruthless, unfeeling nut. 
</P>
<P>
CHET HILL 
</P>
<P>
Arroyo Grande 
</P>
</TEXT>
