<HEADLINE>
<P>
DEPOSIT TICKET WINS SAPLING STAKES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
OCEANPORT, N.J. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Deposit Ticket put away eight other 2-year-olds to turn in a 3 3/4-length 
victory in Saturday's Grade II Sapling Stakes at Monmouth Park. Ridden by Gary 
Stevens, the bay son of Northern Baby covered the six furlongs in 1:11 over a 
muddy track and paid $7.20. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
