MENEM BROTHER HEADS ARGENTINA'S PERONISTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sen. Eduardo Menem, brother of Argentine President Carlos Saul Menem, has 
become the effective leader of the ruling Justicialist (Peronist) Party after 
becoming its vice president Friday night, party sources said Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
Although Carlos Saul Menem was chosen party president by the national council, 
