<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: OXNARD; 
</P>
<P>
SUSPECT ARRESTED IN MAN'S SHOOTING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PSYCHE PASCUAL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An Oxnard man who was shot in the stomach during an argument Saturday was 
hospitalized at St. John's Regional Medical Center, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Ernesto Molina, 42, was taken to the hospital shortly after the 10:36 a.m. 
shooting in the 200 block of South Garfield Avenue, Oxnard Police Lt. Stan 
Myers said. 
</P>
<P>
Ramon Barajas, 59, of Oxnard was arrested on suspicion of attempted murder, 
Myers said. Officers were told that the shooting stemmed from a dispute between 
Barajas' daughter and Molina's wife. A small-caliber gun was found at the 
scene, Myers said. PSYCHE PASCUAL 
</P>
