<HEADLINE>
<P>
CURRENTS: FOOD; 
</P>
<P>
MAGICAL KITCHEN HELPERS FOR BAKERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ROBIN TUCKER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ONCE IN A WHILE something so simple and practical comes along that you wonder 
how you ever got along without it. Take the Von Snedaker Magic Baking Set. 
</P>
<P>
It consists of four non-stick, reusable pieces of Teflon-coated Fiberglas 
pre-cut to fit an eight-inch-square utility pan, a 5x9-inch loaf pan and two 
round nine-inch cake or pie pans. (There is also a Von Snedaker Magic Baking 
Sheet, which measures 17 1/4x14 1/2 inches and fits most cookie sheets.) 
</P>
<P>
No spraying or greasing is necessary when baking (up to 500 degrees) with these 
pieces. Just place one in the desired pan, and cakes, pies and brownies turn 
out with no sticking at all. The Magic Baking Set cleans easily with a damp 
cloth and is microwave- and dishwasher-safe; and the pieces store conveniently 
in their own 9 1/2x12 1/2-inch envelope. 
</P>
<P>
The only prohibition for the magical baking pans is that you can't cut on them; 
a cut scores the finish and makes food stick. But if that should happen, you 
can simply turn the piece over and use the other side. 
</P>
<P>
 The Von Snedaker Magic Baking Set is available at Lawry's Gift Shop, Lawry's 
California Center, 570 West Avenue 26, Los Angeles, (213) 224-6800, and at 
other area cook stores. Or telephone Von Snedaker, (213) 395-6365. 
</P>
<P>
ROBIN TUCKER 
</P>
</TEXT>
