<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE WEEK AHEAD: A LOOK AT UPCOMING EVENTS IN LOS ANGELES COUNTY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
REACHING OUT: A new proposal for a public safety center to house sheriff's 
deputies and community outreach programs in Santa Fe Springs will be discussed 
Monday at a 6 p.m. City Council meeting. 
</P>
<P>
APPEAL CONSIDERED: A Los Angeles Superior Court judge on Tuesday will consider 
the appeal of Billy Joe McIlvain, a former San Gabriel police officer convicted 
of murdering a teen-age gang member in 1977. McIlvain, 45, who is serving a 
life sentence in state prison, contends that jailhouse informants lied at his 
trial to win leniency for themselves. 
</P>
<P>
MULTI-SCREEN THEATER: A proposal for the construction of Long Beach's first 
downtown multi-screen theater project comes before the City Council Tuesday for 
final approval. 
</P>
</TEXT>
