<P>
SAN DIEGO SPORTS ET CETERA: NOMADS FALL OUT OF PLAYOFF CONTENTION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The San Diego Nomads were eliminated from playoff contention in the Western 
Soccer League after 4-1 loss Saturday night to Real Santa Barbara at 
Southwestern College. 
</P>
<P>
Pat Henderson scored the Nomads' only goal with 11:20 left in the game. 
</P>
<P>
The Nomads had 29 shots on goal and finished their season with an 8-12 record. 
</P>
<P>
J.J. Kenzel's goal broke a 1-1 tie as San Dieguito Surf defeated a West German 
team, 2-1, to reach today's semifinals in the boys' 16 division of the San 
Dieguito Surf International tournament. San Dieguito Surf will play the Bonita 
Rebels, and the Alta Loma Arsenal will face the Mission Viejo Pateadores in the 
other semifinal. North Huntington Beach plays the La Jolla Nomads in one boys' 
19 semifinals, Cisco (Phoenix, Ariz) facing San Pedro in the other. 
</P>
<P>
In the girls' 19 semifinals, San Dieguito Surf will play Pegasus Black of 
Rancho Bernardo, and Fountain Valley will play Pegasus White. 
</P>
<P>
BASEBALL 
</P>
<P>
The San Diego Stars, a county all-star team of Pony League players, defended 
their national championship late Friday by defeating Honolulu, 2-1. 
</P>
<P>
The team played 12 games in six days. 
</P>
<P>
In final game, Mario Sanchez of La Mesa scored the winning run on a hit by Jeff 
Dufek of Scripps Ranch. Mission Bay's John Pellegrin was the winning pitcher. 
</P>
<P>
David Myers of La Jolla was the team had an average near .500 for the 
tournament. 
</P>
<P>
Many of the San Diego players will leave on Wednesday for the USSR to help 
train Soviet youths in the sport. 
</P>
