<HEADLINE>
<P>
GRAND OPENINGS: 8 HOMES NEAR TRACK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Village Arcadia, a 20-unit gated development of eight three-bedroom 
single-family houses and 12 three-bedroom duplex units, opens today in Arcadia 
east of the Santa Anita Race Track. Offered in three two-story floor plans 
ranging in size from 2,002 to 2,316 square feet, the houses by Century Pacific 
Associates are priced from $229,900 to $399,900. 
</P>
<P>
Features include 2 1/2 baths, cathedral ceilings, wood-burning fireplaces, 
plant shelves, utility rooms, walk-in closets, private patios and two-car 
garages with roll-up doors and automatic openers. 
</P>
<P>
Move-ins are planned for Sept. 15. There is a $135 monthly association fee. Two 
models are open daily from 11 a.m. to 6 p.m. at 420 E. California St., reached 
from the southbound Santa Anita Avenue exit of the Foothill (210) Freeway. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
Aliso Viejo Homes 
</P>
<P>
Seacoast Terrace, with 186 single-family houses by Kathryn G. Thompson 
Development Co., opens today in the Laguna Audubon planned community in Orange 
County's Aliso Viejo. 
</P>
<P>
The first phase of 18 three- and four-bedroom houses is available in three 
plans, ranging from 1,634 to 1,841 square feet, priced from $229,900 to 
$249,900. There is a monthly association fee of $79.04. Laguna Audubon has no 
connection, directly or indirectly, with, nor is it sponsored by the National 
Audubon Society or any of its affiliates. 
</P>
<P>
First move-ins are planned for February. Three furnished models are open from 
10 a.m. to 6 p.m. daily at 2 Golden Eagle Court, reached from the Laguna Canyon 
Road exit of the San Diego (5) Freeway. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
