<HEADLINE>
<P>
A BERLIN BASH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Some Germans were confused, and some enjoyed the sport for its "spectacle," but 
55,429 got a taste of American football Saturday at Olympiastadion. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Kansas City's Jonathan Hayes (85), Rod Jones (91), Stephone Paige, (83), 
emerge from the tunnel at Olympiastadion at the start of American Bowl '90. The 
banner above them means, 'Berlin is good for us.' The game wasn't good for the 
Chiefs, who lost, 19-3, to the Rams. Associated Press; Photo, It's a sign of 
