<HEADLINE>
<P>
BEST BETS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE RAMOS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Pop and country singer Kenny Rogers brings his special crossover blend of the 
Nashville sound to Norwalk Saturday, where he will perform at 8 p.m. at the 
Cerritos College stadium, 11110 Alondra Blvd. The concert featuring the 
white-bearded country crooner will be presented by Cerritos College and the 
Bellflower Chamber of Commerce. 
</P>
<P>
Chamber staff members said they have been working more than a year to set up a 
concert headlining Rogers, who has been a regular on the Top 40 charts for the 
past decade. 
</P>
<P>
Rogers is pictured above during a concert in 1988 at the Celebrity Theatre in 
Anaheim. 
</P>
<P>
A portion of the Cerritos concert proceeds will benefit the 1990 Cerebral Palsy 
Spastic Children's Foundation, the Cerritos YMCA, Little House, Su Casa, Pools 
for the Handicapped and the Associated Students of Cerritos College fund for 
improvements to the stadium track. 
</P>
<P>
Tickets are $20 and $25 for stadium seating, $35 and $50 for assigned seating 
and are on sale at Cerritos College Community Services (860-2451) and through 
the Bellflower Chamber of Commerce (867-1744). 
</P>
<P>
"It's yuppified boxing," says Steve Brooks, head of West Coast Pro Sports, 
which is presenting "Boxing by the Beach" at 7:30 p.m. Wednesday in the Grand 
Ballroom of the Hyatt Regency Hotel in Long Beach. 
</P>
<P>
"We cater to local businessmen, the coat-and-tie crowd," Brooks said. "They 
come for drinks, to see the ring girls and to see two guys brawling." 
</P>
<P>
Wednesday's five-bout card will be headed by Esias Zumudio, the North American 
Boxing Federation world flyweight champion, who will face an opponent as yet 
unnamed. 
</P>
<P>
Tickets are $20 for general admission, $40 for VIP seats and $75 for ringside. 
They can be purchased at 4136 Anaheim St., Long Beach. For more information, 
call 494-4886. MIKE RAMOS 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, KENNY ROGERS R. VERONICA DECKER / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
