<LENGTH>
<P>
567 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROLL CALL: THE HOUSE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Debt Ceiling Increase 
</P>
<P>
The House voted 221 to 205 to raise the federal debt limit by $332 billion, 
from $3.122 trillion to $3.444 trillion. The new ceiling (HR 5355) is expected 
to give the government borrowing authority to pay its bills through the end of 
fiscal 1991 on Sept. 30, 1991. 
</P>
<P>
Supporter Robert H. Michel (R-Ill.) said Congress "could cause a governmental 
disaster" by rejecting the bill. Opponent Robert T. Matsui (D-Sacramento) said 
President Bush now knows "the actual deficit of this country is $300 billion a 
year, not the $64 billion that in January he talked about" in his 1991 budget. 
</P>
<P>
A yes vote was to hike federal borrowing by $332 billion. 
</P>
